mit was intended as a venue for resolving differences among its members. As a practical matter, the summit was also conceived as an opportunity for its members to give each other mutual encouragement in the face of difficult economic decisions.<ref name=\"reinalda205\"/>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery widths=\"145px\">\nFile:Mulroney.jpg|{{flagicon|Canada}} '''[[Canada]]'''<br />[[Brian Mulroney]], [[Prime Minister of Canada|Prime Minister]]\nFile:Reagan Mitterrand 1984 (cropped).jpg|{{flagicon|France}} '''[[France]]'''<br />[[Fran\u00e7ois Mitterrand]], [[President of France|President]]\nFile:Bundesarchiv B 145 Bild-F074398-0021 Kohl (cropped).jpg|{{flagicon|Germany}} '''[[Germany]]'''<br />[[Helmut Kohl]], [[Chancellor of Germany (Federal Republic)|Chancellor]]\nFile:Bettino Craxi 2.jpg|{{flagicon|Italy}} '''[[Italy]]'''<br />[[Bettino Craxi]], [[Prime Minister of Italy|Prime Minister]]\nFile:Yasuhiro Nakasone in Andrews cropped.jpg|{{flagicon|Japan}} '''[[Japan]]'''<br />[[Yasuhiro Nakasone]], [[Prime Minister of Japan|Prime Minister]]\nFile:Margaret Thatcher (1983).jpg|{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} '''[[United Kingdom]]'''<br />[[Margaret Thatcher]], [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom|Prime Minister]]\nFile:Official Portrait of President Reagan 1981-cropped.jpg|{{flagicon|United States}} '''[[United States]]'''<br />[[Ronald Reagan]], [[President of the United States|President]]\nFile:Bundesarchiv B 145 Bild-F078267-0023, Bonn, Ministerpr\u00e4sidenten mit EU-Kommissar Delors-CROPPED.jpg|{{flagicon|EU}} '''[[European Community]]'''<br />[[Jacques Delors]], [[President of the European Commission|Commission President]]\nFile:Ruud Lubbers 1986.jpg|{{flagicon|EU}} '''[[European Community]]'''<br />[[Ruud Lubbers]], [[Prime Minister of the Netherlands]], rotating [[Presidency of the Council of the European Union|Council President]]\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[G8]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==References==\n* Bayne, Nicholas and Robert D. Putnam. (2000). [https:/