{"title_page": "Omophron", "text_new": "{{short description|Genus of beetles}}\n{{italic title}}\n{{Taxobox\n| name = ''Omophron''\n| image = Omophron tessellatum.jpg\n| image_caption = ''Omophron tessellatum''\n| regnum = [[Animal]]ia\n| phylum = [[Arthropod]]a\n| classis = [[Insect]]a\n| ordo = [[Beetle|Coleoptera]]\n| subordo = [[Adephaga]]\n| familia = [[Carabidae]]\n| subfamilia = '''Omophroninae'''\n| subfamilia_authority = [[Franco Andrea Bonelli|Bonelli]], 1810\n| genus = '''''Omophron'''''\n| genus_authority = [[Latreille]], 1802\n| synonyms =\n''Omophoron'' <small>(''[[lapsus]]'')</small>\n}}\n[[file:Omophron nitidum P1440156a.jpg|thumb|''Omophron nitidum'']]\n\n'''''Omophron''''' is a genus of [[ground beetle]] (Carabidae), the only extant genus in the subfamily '''Omophroninae'''. It is mostly distributed in the Northern Hemisphere with the southern border running through [[Guatemala]] and [[Hispaniola]] in Americas, [[South Africa]] and [[Madagascar]] in Africa, [[Malaysia]] and [[Philippines]] in Asia.<ref name=valantis>{{cite journal|first=Uldis|last=Valainis|year=2010|title=A review of genus ''Omophron'' Latreille, 1802 (Coleoptera: Carabidae) Palearctic fauna and distribution|journal=Baltic Journal of Coleopterology|volume=10|issue=2|pages=105\u2013128 |url=http://www.bjc.sggw.waw.pl/arts/2010v10n2/1.pdf |format=PDF}}</ref>\n\n==Species==\n\n''Omophron'' contains 68 species divided into two subgenera:<ref name=carabidae.org>{{cite web|url=http://carabidae.org/carabidae/omophron-latreille-1802-89.html|title=List of ''Omophron'' species|work=Carabidae of the World|publisher=Institute of Systematic Biology (Daugavpils University)|accessdate=12 November 2012}}</ref>\n\n'''Subgenus ''Omophron'' <small>Latriele, 1802</small>'''\n{{Columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n* ''[[Omophron aequale]]'' <small>Morawitz, 1863</small>\n* ''[[Omophron affine]]'' <small>Banninger, 1918</small>\n* ''[[Omophron africanum]]'' <small>Rousseau, 1908</small>\n* ''[[Omophron amandae]