 1889]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Rutherford,_New_Jersey"}
{"title_page": "El clon", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name          = El clon\n| image              = El-clon-poster.jpg\n| genre              = [[Telenovela]]\n| creator            = {{Plainlist|\n* Roberto Stopello\n* Sandra Velasco\n}}\n| based_on           = {{based on|''[[O Clone]]''|[[Gl\u00f3ria Perez]]}}\n| director           = {{Plainlist|\n* Mauricio Cruz\n* Agustin Restrepo\n}}\n| creative_director  = Gabriela Monroy\n| starring           = {{Plainlist|<!-- Organized by broadcast credit order, with new main cast added to the end of the list -->\n* [[Mauricio Ochmann]]\n* [[Sandra Echeverr\u00eda]]\n* [[Sa\u00fal Lisazo]]\n* [[Roberto Moll]]\n* [[Geraldine Zivic]]\n* [[Andrea L\u00f3pez]]\n* [[Juan Pablo Raba]]\n* [[Daniel Lugo (actor)|Daniel Lugo]]\n}}\n| music              = {{Plainlist|\n* Oliver Camargo\n* Jos\u00e9 Carlos Mar\u00eda\n* Nicol\u00e1s Uribe\n}}\n| opentheme          = \n| language           = Spanish\n| num_seasons        = 1\n| num_episodes       = 184\n| executive_producer = [[Hugo Le\u00f3n Ferrer]]\n| cinematography     = {{Plainlist|\n* Eduardo Carre\u00f1o\n* Alfredo Zamudio\n}}\n| editor             = Alba Merchan Hamann\n| camera             = [[Multi-camera]]\n| runtime            = <!-- Reliable source required -->\n| location           = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Fez, Morocco|Fez]], [[Morocco]]\n* [[Miami]], [[Florida]], [[United States]]\n* [[Bogot\u00e1]], [[Colombia]]\n}}\n| company            = {{Plainlist|\n* [[RTI Producciones]]\n* [[Rede Globo|Rede Globo de Televis\u00e3o]]\n* [[Telemundo Studios]]\n}}\n| distributor        = [[Telemundo Internacional]]\n| network            = [[Telemundo]]\n| picture_format     = [[NTSC]] ([[480i]])\n| audio_format       = [[Stereophonic sound]]\n| first_aired        = {{Start date|2010|2|15}}\n| last_aired         = {{End date|2010|10|29}}\n| preceded_by        = ''[[M\u00e1s sabe el diablo]]''\n| followed_by        = ''[[Aurora (telenovela)|Aurora]]''\n| related            = ''[[O Clone]]'' (Brazilian version)\n| website            = <!-- Remove or comment out this parameter line completely if URL exists on or is moved to Wikidata -->\n}}\n'''''El Clon''''' (The Clone) is a Spanish-language [[telenovela]] released in 2010, produced by the [[United States|U.S.]]-based [[television]] network [[Telemundo]], the [[Colombia]]n network [[Caracol Television]] and the [[Brazil]]ian network [[Rede Globo|Globo]].<ref name=\"variety\">[http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117985497.html?categoryId=14&cs=1 Variety \u2013 Telemundo teams on telenovela]</ref> It is a remake of ''[[O Clone]]'', a [[Brazil]]ian telenovela that originally aired on Globo in 2001 and on Telemundo in 2002.<ref name=\"variety\" /> This limited run melodrama, which starred [[Mauricio Ochmann]] and [[Sandra Echeverr\u00eda]],<ref name=\"elnuevodia\">http://www.elnuevodia.com/encaminadalaversionhispanadeelclon-623393.html</ref> deals with topics such as [[drug trafficking]], [[cloning]] and [[Islam]].<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/televisionNews/idUSN1256382420080512 Reuters \u2013 Telemundo revives \"El Clon\" for U.S. Latino market]</ref>\n\nTelemundo executive Mark Santana called ''El Clon'' \"the most ambitious telenovela in the history of television\".<ref name=\"elnuevodia\" /> This melodrama features a love triangle featuring Lucas, a handsome hero, challenging his clone for the love of an enticing, exotic woman. Lucas is young when he falls for a young [[Arab]] girl named Jade. She is caught between modern values and her Islamic upbringing. They separate and two decades pass. Then a strange turn of luck brings the pair together. Then Jade meets the clone, who is just like Lucas, but twenty years younger. She must choose between the man she loved and the memory she cherishes.\n\n== History ==\nThe remake debuted on February 15, 2010.<ref name=\"elnuevodia\" /> It was filmed in [[Fes|Fez]], [[Morocco]], with some scenes shot on location in the [[Middle East]], and in [[Bogot\u00e1]], where Girardot's city represents Fez and [[Miami]],<ref name=\"elnuevodia\" /> although the main setting is Miami.<ref>[http://www.broadcastingcable.com/article/CA6559914.html Broadcasting & Cable \u2013 Upfront: Telemundo Details Telenovelas]</ref> It includes several members of the original production team, including screenwriter [[Gl\u00f3ria Perez]] and director [[Jayme Monjardim]].<ref>[http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/showtracker/2008/05/upfronts-telemu.html LA Times \u2013 Upfronts: Telemundo announces fall lineup]</ref>\n\nAs part of the 2010 season, [[Telemundo]] aired the serial weeknights at 8pm/7c central, replacing ''[[M\u00e1s Sabe el Diablo]]''. The series ended with a two-hour finale on October 29, 2010 with ''[[Aurora (Telenovela)|Aurora]]'' replacing it. As with most of its other soap operas, the network broadcasts [[Telemundo#English subtitles|English subtitles]] as closed captions on CC3. As part of the production deal, [[Rede Globo|Globo]] agreed to [[embargo]] distribution of the original Portuguese version for five years.\n\n== Plot ==\n{{Long plot|section|date=April 2020}}\nThe telenovela tells the story of Jade and Lucas. Jade is a young woman of Arab descent, who has to live with her father's family in Morocco after the death of her mother. Lucas is a young romantic, and son of a powerful businessman. When Lucas is on vacation in Morocco, he meets Jade, and the two of them fall in love. However, cultural differences do not allow them to be together.\n\ntelenovela tells the story of Jade and Lucas. Jade is a young woman of Arab descent, who is supposed to live with her father's family in Morocco after the death of her mother. Lucas is a young romantic, and son of a powerful businessman, Leonardo Ferrer. When Lucas is on vacation in Morocco, he meets Jade, and the two of them fall in love. However, cultural differences do not allow them to be together.\n\n== Cast and characters ==\n{| 